 Therefore, solving the UMP and the EMP will give you the same bundle of
 goods.
 However, then the question becomes, why do we need two representations
 of the same solution? The short answer is that the two functions take different
 arguments (wealth in the Walrasian, and fixed utility in the Hicksian)
 and so will behave differently to changes in the parameter values.
 Let's look at the relationship between the two and why the Hicksian is
 sometimes referred to as the compensated demand function.
\end_layout

