Notice that a 10% tax would result in the following price vectors (depending
 on whether apples or bananas are taxed): 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{p}^{a}=\left[{p_{a}^{a}\atop p_{b}^{a}}\right]=\left[{1.1\atop 2}\right]$
