 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{p}^{b}=\left[{p_{a}^{b}\atop p_{b}^{b}}\right]=\left[{1\atop 2.2}\right]$
\end_inset

.
 Let's use the notation 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{p}^{0}=\left[{p_{a}^{0}\atop p_{b}^{0}}\right]=\left[{1\atop 2}\right]$
\end_inset

 to denote the pre-tax price.
 Further, let's denote the level of utility at the original prices 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\vec{p}^{0}\right)$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{u}^{0}$
\end_inset

; at apple tax prices 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\vec{p}^{a}\right)$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{u}^{a}$
\end_inset

; and at banana tax prices 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\vec{p}^{b}\right)$
\end_inset

 as 
